article.headline: Temple 83, St. Bonaventure 66
article.story: OLEAN, N.Y. (AP) -- Mark Tyndale scored 26 points to lead Temple to an 83-66 win over St. Bonaventure on Wednesday night. Mardy Collins added 17 points, while Antywane Robinson had 14. Dustin Salisbery and Wayne Marshall scored 10 apiece for the Owls (7-6, 1-2 Atlantic 10). Michael Lee led the Bonnies (6-8, 0-3) with 16 points. Paul Williams had his fourth double-double in five games with 12 points and 16 rebounds. Trailing 64-42 with just under 15 minutes in the second half, the Bonnies managed a 13-6 spurt. But the Owls took back control with dunks by Tyndale and Salisbery. Temple went on a 17-7 run in the first half, capped with a 3-pointer by Robinson, to go up 50-33 at the break. The Owls scored more points in the first half than their total points in two other games this season. Before the game, St. Bonaventure coach Anthony Solomon suspended Patrick Lottin for an undetermined period because he failed to meet the team's "established standards." Lottin was averaging 10 points and 5.6 rebounds. Solomon declined to elaborate on the reason for the suspension.
